    "name": "Dreadstone Keep",
    "steam_appid": 2296120,
    "required_age": 0,
    "is_free": false,
    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/1397a0565451cc2d2ba5508c8252c2e8.webp?t=1770064188\" width=291 height=24 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><i>The high spires of the Keep have loomed over your village since untold ages. Now, with the Dark Powers that dwell into it menacing your people, a folk hero must rise to defeat them!</i></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/eedca137ced0b15bd3f40b4d0b929b52.poster.avif?t=1770064188\" width=600 height=118 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/eedca137ced0b15bd3f40b4d0b929b52.webm?t=1770064188\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Dreadstone Keep</strong> is a roguelike, strategy turn-based game where you must defeat the two powerful entities that rule the ancient castle. Acquire upgrades, use your wits and battle powerful pixel art enemies. With one Dark Power at the top and another at the bottom of the fortress, will you be powerful enough to ensure peace and prosperity for your people?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/945a01b4180f9f958e07b611ea6cf350.webp?t=1770064188\" width=132 height=21 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You don't have to rush to make your decisions, so make them wisely. The creatures that dwell into the keep are as unforgiving as they are powerful. With enemies ranging from skeletons to vampires and even necromancers, the threats are great and the stakes are high.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/29a86a777abf8883d8f0b34b51d16c28.poster.avif?t=1770064188\" width=600 height=144 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/29a86a777abf8883d8f0b34b51d16c28.webm?t=1770064188\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/2fd32f049c7bec35d42fc4602c684747.webp?t=1770064188\" width=159 height=21 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >You may start your run going to the top of the Keep or to the depths of it's dungeons, facing different areas and biomes in each of them. Choose what fits better into your strategy.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/662b51065fa2c0933ba3525f8b404c7c.poster.avif?t=1770064188\" width=600 height=192 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/662b51065fa2c0933ba3525f8b404c7c.webm?t=1770064188\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/6157cb8f5bfd78719510fe51781edcea.webp?t=1770064188\" width=282 height=21 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Make your character a fitting adversary to the Dark Powers through many powerful upgrades, ranging from the <strong>Rogue Demilich</strong> companion to the unpredictable <strong>Orb of Unstable Teleportation</strong>! Will your build be one that focuses on hit and run, perhaps throwing your weapon away and going melee against your enemies, or even something completely different?</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/94e0e63a64ef66c72f8971b3be60698a.poster.avif?t=1770064188\" width=600 height=318 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2296120/extras/94e0e63a64ef66c72f8971b3be60698a.webm?t=1770064188\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p>",
